# Code Implementation

**IMPORTANT**: Create/edit/refactor code → MUST use coder agent. Task tool `subagent_type: "coder"`.

## When

Coder agent for:
- New features
- Bug fixes
- Refactor
- Multi-file changes
- Functions, classes, components
- Any write/edit code

## How

```javascript
// ❌ WRONG: Making code changes directly
StrReplace(...)

// ✅ CORRECT: Spawn coder agent for implementation
Task({
  subagent_type: "coder",  // .cursor/agents/coder.md — PublishPress Future coder
  prompt: "Read .cursor/skills/coding-agent/SKILL.md. Then: [task]",
  description: "3-5 word summary"
})
```

## Exceptions

Direct edit OK only:
- Read files (understand code)
- Docs (README, etc.)
- Config files
- Minor single-line fix (typo, simple correction)

## Benefits

Coder agent:
- Project standards auto
- Best practices consistent
- Multi-file systematic
- Better error handling + validation
- Thorougher impl
